  "headline20": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 18 airports right now.",
  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 18 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 critical, 6 high, 13 medium, 14 normal. Key bases needing attention include Sibiu (SBZ/LRSB), Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR) and Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE); plus 9 other bases. 13 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Modlin (WMI/EPMO). Network hotspots: Turku (TKU/EFTU), Maastricht Aachen (MST/EHBK), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and 13 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 6 airports changed status, led by Turku (TKU/EFTU), Kaunas (KUN/EYKA), Palanga (PLQ/EYPA) and 3 others.",
  "detail90": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 18 airports right now. Base airports (focus): Sibiu (SBZ/LRSB) — HIGH: mist; snow; cold-temperature performance penalties | Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR) — HIGH: fog; visibility down to 600 m, cloud base around 200 ft | Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE) — CRIT: mist; snow; cloud base around 200 ft | Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) — HIGH: mist; snow; cold-temperature performance penalties | Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) — CRIT: mist; snow; strong gusts risk | Modlin (WMI/EPMO) — CRIT: fog; snow; visibility down to 400 m, cloud base around 100 ft and 6 others. Worst affected now: Turku (TKU/EFTU) — CRIT: snow; cold-temperature performance penalties; strong gusts risk (drivers: runway visual range (RVR) constraints, cold-temperature performance penalties, very low visibility) | Maastricht Aachen (MST/EHBK) — CRIT: mist; visibility down to 2.4 km, cloud base around 100 ft (drivers: low ceilings, thunderstorm/convective risk, mist) | Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR) — CRIT: mist; snow; visibility down to 1.2 km, cloud base around 200 ft (drivers: low ceilings, mist, snow/blowing snow) | Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) — CRIT: freezing fog; snow; visibility down to 300 m (drivers: low-visibility procedures (reduced capacity), runway visual range (RVR) constraints, approach minima limits) | Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) — CRIT: mist; snow; strong gusts risk (drivers: low ceilings, mist, snow/blowing snow) | Modlin (WMI/EPMO) — CRIT: fog; snow; visibility down to 400 m, cloud base around 100 ft (drivers: low-visibility takeoff restrictions, runway visual range (RVR) constraints, very low visibility) and 12 others. Changed since last run: Turku (TKU/EFTU), Kaunas (KUN/EYKA), Palanga (PLQ/EYPA), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Ohrid St. Paul the Apostle (OHD/LWOH), Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI).",
